      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RACING WRITER (1) continued his good form when he raced parked from a wider barrier but stuck on for fourth last start at Temora. Had been runner-up in his previous two outings, beaten just a neck at this circuit and distance two back. Likely to get the favours from the ace draw so could break through. MAGIC MATTEO (4) has joined the Mat Rue stable since he last raced three-and-a-half months ago. Looks forward enough for the return after a minor placing in a recent trial. Could make an immediate impact. ULTIMATE EGO (5) has to come into calculations on the back of some consistent form, adding to a series of top-four finishes when off the back line most recently at Leeton. BIDGEE BABE (7) draws for a trail and came from this row when she scored two back at Temora.",
